{
  "$schema": "https://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2019-04-01/deploymentTemplate.json#",
  "contentVersion": "1.0.0.0",
  "parameters": {
    "servicePrincipalName": {
      "type": "string",
      "defaultValue": "AssetCounterSP",
      "metadata": {
        "description": "Name for the service principal"
      }
    },
    "roleAssignmentScope": {
      "type": "string",
      "defaultValue": "[subscription().id]",
      "metadata": {
        "description": "Scope for role assignment (subscription, resource group, or resource)"
      }
    }
  },
  "variables": {
    "readerRoleDefinitionId": "[concat('/subscriptions/', subscription().subscriptionId, '/providers/Microsoft.Authorization/roleDefinitions/', 'acdd72a7-3385-48ef-bd42-f606fba81ae7')]",
    "customRoleDefinitionName": "AssetCounterCustomRole"
  },
  "resources": [
    {
      "type": "Microsoft.Authorization/roleDefinitions",
      "apiVersion": "2022-04-01",
      "name": "[guid(subscription().id, 'AssetCounterRole')]",
      "properties": {
        "roleName": "[variables('customRoleDefinitionName')]",
        "description": "Custom role for Azure Asset Counter with read-only permissions",
        "type": "CustomRole",
        "permissions": [
          {
            "actions": [
              "*/read",
              "Microsoft.Resources/subscriptions/read",
              "Microsoft.Resources/subscriptions/resourceGroups/read",
              "Microsoft.Resources/resources/read",
              "Microsoft.ResourceGraph/resources/read",
              "Microsoft.ResourceGraph/queries/read"
            ],
            "notActions": [],
            "dataActions": [],
            "notDataActions": []
          }
        ],
        "assignableScopes": [
          "[subscription().id]"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "outputs": {
    "customRoleDefinitionId": {
      "type": "string",
      "value": "[resourceId('Microsoft.Authorization/roleDefinitions', guid(subscription().id, 'AssetCounterRole'))]"
    },
    "readerRoleDefinitionId": {
      "type": "string",
      "value": "[variables('readerRoleDefinitionId')]"
    },
    "deploymentInstructions": {
      "type": "string",
      "value": "ARM template deployed. Now create service principal using Azure CLI commands in the comments below."
    }
  }
}

/*
===================================================================================
Azure Service Principal Creation Guide
===================================================================================

METHOD 1: Using Azure CLI (Recommended)
---------------------------------------

Step 1: Create Service Principal with Reader Role
--------------------------------------------------
az ad sp create-for-rbac \
  --name "AssetCounterSP" \
  --role "Reader" \
  --scopes /subscriptions/{subscription-id}

Output will provide:
{
  "appId": "aaaaaaaa-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeeeeeeeeeee",
  "displayName": "AssetCounterSP",
  "password": "your-client-secret",
  "tenant": "tttttttt-tttt-tttt-tttt-tttttttttttt"
}

Step 2: Store Credentials Securely
-----------------------------------
# Add to azure_config.ini:
[default]
auth_method = service_principal
tenant_id = tttttttt-tttt-tttt-tttt-tttttttttttt
client_id = aaaaaaaa-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeeeeeeeeeee
client_secret = your-client-secret


Step 3: Test Service Principal
-------------------------------
az login --service-principal \
  --username aaaaaaaa-bbbb-cccc-dddd-eeeeeeeeeeee \
  --password your-client-secret \
  --tenant tttttttt-tttt-tttt-tttt-tttttttttttt

az account show


METHOD 2: Using Azure Portal
-----------------------------

Step 1: Register Application
-----------------------------
1. Go to Azure Portal > Azure Active Directory
2. Select "App registrations" > "New registration"
3. Name: "AssetCounterSP"
4. Click "Register"
5. Note down:
   - Application (client) ID
   - Directory (tenant) ID

Step 2: Create Client Secret
-----------------------------
1. In the app registration, go to "Certificates & secrets"
2. Click "New client secret"
3. Description: "AssetCounter"
4. Expiration: Choose duration (recommended: 12-24 months)
5. Click "Add"
6. Copy the secret value immediately (won't be shown again)

Step 3: Assign Reader Role
---------------------------
1. Go to Subscriptions > Your Subscription
2. Click "Access control (IAM)"
3. Click "Add role assignment"
4. Role: "Reader"
5. Assign access to: "User, group, or service principal"
6. Select: "AssetCounterSP"
7. Click "Save"

Step 4: Verify Permissions
---------------------------
1. Go to Subscriptions > Your Subscription > "Access control (IAM)"
2. Click "View" under "View access to this resource"
3. Search for "AssetCounterSP"
4. Verify "Reader" role is assigned


METHOD 3: Using PowerShell
---------------------------

Step 1: Create Service Principal
---------------------------------
$sp = New-AzADServicePrincipal -DisplayName "AssetCounterSP" -Role "Reader" -Scope "/subscriptions/{subscription-id}"

$sp | Format-List

# Get credentials
$BSTR = [System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal]::SecureStringToBSTR($sp.Secret)
$clientSecret = [System.Runtime.InteropServices.Marshal]::PtrToStringAuto($BSTR)

Write-Host "Tenant ID: $((Get-AzContext).Tenant.Id)"
Write-Host "Client ID: $($sp.ApplicationId)"
Write-Host "Client Secret: $clientSecret"

Step 2: Test Service Principal
-------------------------------
$securePassword = ConvertTo-SecureString $clientSecret -AsPlainText -Force
$credential = New-Object System.Management.Automation.PSCredential ($sp.ApplicationId, $securePassword)
Connect-AzAccount -ServicePrincipal -Credential $credential -Tenant (Get-AzContext).Tenant.Id


ADDITIONAL CONFIGURATIONS
==========================

Grant Access to Multiple Subscriptions
---------------------------------------
# For each subscription:
az role assignment create \
  --assignee {service-principal-app-id} \
  --role "Reader" \
  --scope /subscriptions/{subscription-id}


Grant Resource Graph Permissions
---------------------------------
az role assignment create \
  --assignee {service-principal-app-id} \
  --role "Reader" \
  --scope /subscriptions/{subscription-id}

# Resource Graph is included in Reader role by default


Grant Access to Specific Resource Groups Only
----------------------------------------------
az role assignment create \
  --assignee {service-principal-app-id} \
  --role "Reader" \
  --resource-group {resource-group-name}


View Current Role Assignments
------------------------------
az role assignment list \
  --assignee {service-principal-app-id} \
  --output table


Rotate Client Secret
--------------------
# Create new secret
az ad sp credential reset \
  --id {service-principal-app-id} \
  --append

# Or replace all secrets
az ad sp credential reset \
  --id {service-principal-app-id}


Delete Service Principal (Cleanup)
-----------------------------------
az ad sp delete --id {service-principal-app-id}


SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
========================

1. Use Certificate Authentication (More Secure)
   --------------------------------------------
   # Create certificate
   $cert = New-SelfSignedCertificate -CertStoreLocation "cert:\CurrentUser\My" \
     -Subject "CN=AssetCounterSP" -KeySpec KeyExchange
   
   # Export certificate
   Export-Certificate -Cert $cert -FilePath "AssetCounterSP.cer"
   
   # Upload to Azure AD
   az ad sp credential reset --id {app-id} --cert @AssetCounterSP.cer

2. Limit Scope to Necessary Subscriptions/Resource Groups

3. Set Secret Expiration (12-24 months maximum)

4. Monitor Service Principal Activity
   az monitor activity-log list --caller {app-id}

5. Implement Secret Rotation Policy

6. Store Secrets in Azure Key Vault (for automation scenarios)

7. Use Managed Identity When Possible (for Azure-hosted applications)


TROUBLESHOOTING
===============

Error: "Insufficient privileges to complete the operation"
---------------------------------------------------------
Solution: You need "Owner" or "User Access Administrator" role to create 
service principals and assign roles.

Error: "The client does not have authorization to perform action"
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Solution: Service principal needs time to propagate (wait 5-10 minutes) or 
verify role assignment is correct.

Error: "AADSTS700016: Application not found in directory"
----------------------------------------------------------
Solution: Wrong tenant ID or application ID. Verify credentials.


USAGE EXAMPLES
==============

Using with Asset Counter Script:
--------------------------------
python azure-asset-counter.py

Configuration in azure_config.ini:
[default]
auth_method = service_principal
tenant_id = your-tenant-id
client_id = your-client-id
client_secret = your-client-secret

[subscriptions]
scan_mode = all


Testing the Configuration:
--------------------------
# Test Azure login
az login --service-principal \
  --username {client-id} \
  --password {client-secret} \
  --tenant {tenant-id}

# List accessible subscriptions
az account list --output table

# Test Resource Graph query
az graph query -q "Resources | summarize count() by type"

===================================================================================
*/







